HEADWORD: Micraster
<hw>Mi*cras"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>mikro`s</grk> small + <?/ star.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A
genus of sea urchins, similar to Spatangus, abounding in the chalk
formation; -- from the starlike disposal of the ambulacral
furrows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

